Average House Prices in Rural Scotland Double, Scotsman Reports

-- B y   T i m   F a r r a n d
-- 
2011-10-04T07:50:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/average-house-prices-in-rural-scotland-double-scotsman-reports.html
Average house prices in rural
 Scotland  doubled in value over the past decade, the Scotsman
reported, citing an annual Bank of Scotland rural housing
review.  Countryside property prices increased from 79,104 pounds in
2001 to 158,923 pounds in 2011, the Scotsman said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tim Farrand at 
 tfarrand@bloomberg.net  